The
Montandoniola
species form a very homogenous group in their general aspect due to some mimeticism with the thrips, their prey, as already noticed (
Bergroth, 1916
;
Risbec, 1951
;
Carayon, 1958
;
Carayon & Ramade 1962
). This mimeticism is more obvious in living specimens (
